source: https://www.hellofresh.co.uk/recipes/tomatoey-pesto-pasta-5bebf7d530006c607f547902
---

Preheat your oven to 200°C and bring a large #saucepan{} of water to the boil with a pinch of
@salt{pinch} for the pasta. Cut the @Tenderstem® Broccoli{150}(stalks cut in half widthways).
Pop the broccoli on a lined #baking tray{} and drizzle with @oil{}, a pinch of salt and
@black pepper{}, toss together and spread out in a single layer. Leave to the side.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} on medium heat. Once hot, add the
@British Pork and Oregano Sausage Meat{225} and cook, whilst breaking up into roughly 2cm
chunks with a #wooden spoon{}. Stir and cook until browned, ~{6-7%minutes}.

Pour the @finely chopped tomatoes with basil{1}, @tomato puree{30} and @water{75} into the
pan with the sausage meat. Mix together, reduce the heat to medium-low and simmer until thick
and tomatoey, ~{12-15%minutes}. Stir occasionally.

Once the sauce is simmering, pop the broccoli on the top shelf of your oven to roast until
soft and charred at the edges, ~{10-12%minutes}. Add the @penne pasta{200} to the pan of
boiling water and cook until al dente, around ~{7-8%minutes}.

> Tip: 'Al dente' simply means the pasta is cooked through but has a tiny bit of firmness
> left in the middle.

Once the wheat pasta is cooked, drain it in a #colander{} and add it to the pan with the
ragu along with two-thirds of both the @grated hard Italian style cheese{40} and the
@green pesto{45}. Stir together until combined. Taste and add salt and pepper if needed.

Spoon the tomatoey pesto wheat pasta into #bowls{} and top with the tenderstem® broccoli,
all of the remaining cheese and a few spoonfuls of the remaining pesto. Enjoy!